<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-11-18T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-11-18T23:00:00-05:00" n="260" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11299: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-19T12:00:00+08:00">November 19,
                                1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November 19—10:10
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>121. The following telegram has been sent to the Legation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“November 19, noon. The U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">Tutuila</hi>
                                    fired upon by rifle fire at mileage 27 above Chenglingki
                                    yesterday. Fire silenced with 27 rounds 3-inch shells and 650
                                    rounds machine gun. Repeated to Department.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>